{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"77eccc3f-7b03-4b32-b16f-153eeaf13a40","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01EETjukFJBPHEkHRRHC6ic3","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Migrating xUnit v2 to v3"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01JDFdkquUYAEUCMtD6SgJH9","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"dotnet --version 2>/dev/null; dotnet nuget list source 2>/dev/null | head -20","description":"Check .NET SDK and NuGet sources","initial_wait":15},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Check .NET SDK and NuGet sources"}],"interactionId":"afc83329-ff0b-4bd2-a5d9-9a5a375517eb","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I understand the project. Let me plan the migration from xUnit.net v2 to v3:\n\n1. **`.csproj` changes**:\n   - Replace `xunit` v2.9.3 with `xunit.v3` (latest v3 package)\n   - Replace `YTest.MTP.XUnit2` with `YTest.MTP.XUnit3` (the MTP runner for v3)\n   - Since xUnit v3 uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively, the runner package changes\n   - Need to add `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>` since xUnit v3 projects are executables\n   - Also need to configure the program entry point with `<GenerateProgramFile>false</GenerateProgramFile>` or specify a custom entry point\n\n2. **`BasicTests.cs` changes**:\n   - The namespace remains `Xunit` for attributes in v3\n   - Tests must be `public` (already satisfied)\n   - `[Fact]` and `[Theory]` attributes continue to work as before\n   - The project structure needs `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>` since v3 runs as an executable\n\nFor the migration itself, I need to update the package reference from `xunit` to `xunit.v3` and verify the current stable version—v3 was initially released as `0.6.0` series but may be at `1.0.0` or higher by now. The main structural change is converting the test project into an executable format with a proper entry point. I need to figure out what `YTest.MTP.XUnit2` is—it looks like a custom test platform adapter—and find its v3 equivalent. For the migration, I'll need to update the project file to reference `xunit.v3` instead of the v2 package, swap out the adapter for `YTest.MTP.XUnit3`, and add the executable output type. The test code itself should mostly carry over since `[Fact]` and `Assert` remain in the `Xunit` namespace, though I should verify the assertion methods work the same way in v3.\n\nLet me check what .NET SDK versions are available and look up the correct package versions for this migration.","outputTokens":1112,"requestId":"B82E:20FD4A:3095382:336B78F:6A04956A"},"id":"96361fca-90b3-4840-bea8-03de1fe95d30","timestamp":"2026-05-13T15:15:12.424Z","parentId":"d069dc39-9e0d-4554-b9c9-ec8190b23d6f"}
